text: Whitestone is an unincorporated community and census-designated place in Southeast Fairbanks Census Area, Alaska, United States. Its population was 97 as of the 2010 census. This is not to be confused with Whitestone Logging Camp CDP in the Alaskan panhandle. ==Geography== According to the U.S. Census Bureau, the community has an area of , all of it land. ==Demographics== Whitestone first appeared on the 2010 U.S. Census as a census-designated place (CDP). ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Southeast Fairbanks Census Area, Alaska Category:Unincorporated communities in Alaska Category:Census-designated places in Southeast Fairbanks Census Area, Alaska Category:Census-designated places in Alaska
